{"word":"θηράω","slug":"θηράω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θηράω</b></el> <el>(θηράω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θήρα'><el>θήρα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hunt</i> or <i>chase</i> wild beasts, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—of men, <i>to catch, capture</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to captivate</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <el>θ. πόλιν</el> <i>to seek to destroy</i> it, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>venari, to hunt after</el> a thing, <i>pursue</i> it <i>eagerly</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to seek</i> or <i>endeavour</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; and in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> much like <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <i>to hunt for, fish for</i>, <el>ἐγχέλεις</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>οἱ θηρώμενοι</el> <i>hunters</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to cast about for, seek after</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be hunted, pursued</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}